node.text: Anger? Sadness? Confusion? I can’t even come up with words to describe what I’m feeling right now. Believe what you want and say what you want but the facts are clear as day light without a cloud in sight. There are no polls or Emails or he said or she said. That facts are that we as a Country lost 13 brave young souls. We lost 13 men and woman that put themselves before hundreds of thousands of us. Crazy to see that the idiotic crate challenge gets more attention than news like this. We need to reanalyze what’s truly going on here. This country was once feared and with this act it shows just how much we are no longer feared, specially after our response after this incident happened. I love the country that gave me a chance to be someone, the country that has given me a safe and none communistic laws. The country that has allowed me to grow and provide a better life for my family. To all our men and woman who severed and to many that passed, I just want to say thank you for making all that possible. God bless America. I love my country 🇺🇸
